Finally, the Gibbs free energies for fluoridation of boronic acid moieties were calculated (Fig. 9
                        ). The calculated Gibbs free energies vary from −244.2kcalmol−1for X=SH to −310.44kcalmol−1 for X=NH(Me)+
                        2. The agreement between theory and experiment is confirmed again where the reaction for absorber with larger Hammet constant is thermodynamically more favorable with more negative Gibbs free energy.
